T1  - Steady State Solution of the Queue M/Ek/r
AU  - Mayhugh, J. O.
AU  - Mccormick, R. E.
Y1  - 1968/07/01
PY  - 1968
DA  - 1968/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.14.11.692
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.14.11.692
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 692
EP  - 712
VL  - 14
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The multiserver queue with Poisson arrivals and Erlangian, gamma or chi-square service time is solved for the steady state case. A general procedure, adaptable to computer programming, for writing the equations for the state probabilities is given. Generating functions for the time invariant state probabilities are found. A method of computing numerical solutions is described.
AB  - The multiserver queue with Poisson arrivals and Erlangian, gamma or chi-square service time is solved for the steady state case. A general procedure, adaptable to computer programming, for writing the equations for the state probabilities is given. Generating functions for the time invariant state probabilities are found. A method of computing numerical solutions is described.
